@smnmtzgr Yes, I don't think we should do anything here. The default on the NEXUS is to have this disabled so someone would have had to enable this.

An alternate fix would be to send a direct command to unconfigure this and then reconfigure this at the end of the session. 

You would have to override the default code, however, as the initial connection fails.

