Note that you shouldn't *have* to call ``set_global_log_level()`` at all (but I haven't tested this since @hawkowl's most recent changes). If you're using twisted's logger yourself, it should work like this:

 - a txaio logger gets, e.g., a .debug() message;
 - txaio emits this message;
 - then your observer sees it and takes action according to its level.

If you call ``txaio.set_global_log_level()`` then your observer simply won't see an "over level" message at all (i.e. it's never emitted, because ``.debug()`` became a no-op).

