IIRC, there can be only one Pulp database, right? If that's the case, then maybe something like this would be more appropriate:

```json
{
    "default": {
        "base_url": "https://localhost",
        "auth": [
            "admin",
            "admin"
        ],
        "database": {
            "hostname": "pulp-db.example.com",
            "username": "pulp-db-admin"
        },
        "verify": false
    }
}
```

And the `database` section does not need to be specified in the configuration file. In the application itself, `hostname` can be inferred from `base_url` if omitted, and `username` can be taken from the environment if omitted.

