I was using master branch.

Regarding utf8 vs utf-8, from python source code utf-8 handled by PyUnicode_Decode differently from {utf8,utf_8}, see snippet below:
```c++
PyUnicode_Decode(...)
{
   if (encoding == NULL)
       encoding = PyUnicode_GetDefaultEncoding();

   /* Shortcuts for common default encodings */
   if (strcmp(encoding, "utf-8") == 0)
       return PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(s, size, errors);
   else if (strcmp(encoding, "latin-1") == 0)
        return PyUnicode_DecodeLatin1(s, size, errors);
   else if..
   ...
    /* Decode via the codec registry */
  ...
       unicode = _PyCodec_DecodeText(buffer, encoding, errors);
...
}
```
when encoding is utf-8 then PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8 is called, when encoding is utf8 or utf_8, then _PyCodec_DecodeText is called.

