@cburgdorf Good to know, thanks. I believe yarn was the original inspiration for using "lockfile" but for the purposes of py-ethpm and the ethpm-spec in general the choice was to rename "lockfile" to "package":
https://github.com/ethpm/ethpm-spec/issues/73

I'm not sure if there's a better way to distinguish between which version of the ethpm-spec the "package" conforms to with the version of the package itself?

