One more important remark regarding the behavior or parameters, which I'm not sure is correct. Say we have a model:

```Modelica
model A
    parameter Real n = 3;
    Real z[n];
end A;

model B
    A a[3];
end B;

model NestedArrayExpressions
    B b;
end NestedArrayExpressions;

model ArrayExpressions
    NestedArrayExpressions nested2[2];
equation
    nested2[1].b.a[1].z[0] = nested2.b.a.n;
    nested2[1].b.a[1].z[0] = nested2[1].b.a[1].n;
end ArrayExpressions;
```
Which of the two equations is correct? The CasADi backend behaves like the above line, assuming that only one (shared) parameter `n` exists for all instances of `A`.
